-- Vietnam, South Korea Agree on Thermal Energy, Mineral Projects, News Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-12-21T01:55:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-21/vietnam-south-korea-agree-on-thermal-energy-mineral-projects-news-says.html
Vietnam and South Korea have agreed
to co-operate in the energy and minerals industries, including
the construction of a $4.5 billion power plant, Vietnam News
reported without citing sources.  The two countries set up a joint venture to build a 2,400
megawatt thermal power plant, and plan to co-operate in
exploiting the Bao Dai coal mine, the paper said. Other
agreements included expansion of cooperation in oil and gas
exploration and exploitation in Vietnam and abroad, and research
into rare minerals, the paper added.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jan Dahinten at 
 jdahinten@bloomberg.net  